The paper focuses on the impact factors of trust in a collaborative manufacturing scenario with a real robot, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the study involves human-robot interaction and evaluation of trust, which are relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The use of objective and subjective measures to evaluate trust also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the study involves the performance and reliability of the robot, which are relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
